1
00:02:16,428 --> 00:02:18,772
Shall I tell you a secret, Séverine?

2
00:02:20,807 --> 00:02:22,901
I love you more every day.

3
00:02:23,018 --> 00:02:24,611
And I you, Pierre.

4
00:02:24,728 --> 00:02:27,151
You're all I have, but -

5
00:02:27,272 --> 00:02:28,819
But what?

6
00:02:29,941 --> 00:02:34,697
I'd like everything to be perfect too.
If only you weren't so cold.

7
00:02:34,821 --> 00:02:36,823
Please don't mention that again.

8
00:02:37,407 --> 00:02:39,501
I didn't mean to upset you.

9
00:02:39,826 --> 00:02:41,999
I feel a great tenderness for you.

10
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:44,631
What good is your tenderness to me?

11
00:02:46,375 --> 00:02:49,003
You can be very cruel
when you wish.

12
00:02:50,462 --> 00:02:52,430
Forgive me, Pierre.

13
00:02:58,303 --> 00:02:59,805
Stop.

14
00:03:09,314 --> 00:03:10,657
Get out.

15
00:03:10,774 --> 00:03:13,573
- What's going on?
- I said get out.

16
00:03:13,694 --> 00:03:15,116
But why?

17
00:03:15,237 --> 00:03:16,204
Come on.

18
00:03:16,321 --> 00:03:19,621
- Let me go!
- Come on!

19
00:03:22,661 --> 00:03:24,504
Do what I told you.

20
00:03:33,714 --> 00:03:35,557
How dare you!

21
00:03:35,799 --> 00:03:37,472
Let me go!

22
00:03:39,094 --> 00:03:40,767
You brutes!

23
00:03:41,388 --> 00:03:43,106
Let go of me!

24
00:03:44,725 --> 00:03:48,480
It's not my fault.
I can explain everything.

25
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:51,068
Go on.

26
00:03:51,189 --> 00:03:54,193
Don't worry about roughing up
the little slut! Hurry!

27
00:03:54,317 --> 00:03:56,069
Pierre, it's your fault too.

28
00:03:56,236 --> 00:03:58,489
I can explain everything!

29
00:03:58,613 --> 00:04:01,958
Shut your mouth, madame,
or <i>I'll</i> shut it for you!

30
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:11,252
Stop!

31
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:14,554
Please tell them to let me go!

32
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:21,762
Help!

33
00:04:22,304 --> 00:04:23,977
Shut up, you little bitch!

34
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:28,068
Come on.

35
00:04:33,482 --> 00:04:34,984
Pull.

36
00:04:39,237 --> 00:04:41,706
Don't scream or I'll kill you,
you hear?

37
00:04:42,282 --> 00:04:44,455
Pierre, I beg you.

38
00:04:44,576 --> 00:04:46,453
I beg your forgiveness

39
00:04:46,828 --> 00:04:48,501
with all my heart.

40
00:05:03,553 --> 00:05:06,523
Pierre, please don't let the cats out!

41
00:05:22,781 --> 00:05:26,035
That's enough.
She's yours now.

42
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:28,207
- Pierre, I love you!
- Go ahead.

43
00:05:37,671 --> 00:05:39,514
<i>What are you
thinking about, Séverine?</i>

44
00:05:44,010 --> 00:05:45,978


45
00:05:47,764 --> 00:05:50,859
I was thinking about you... and us.

46
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:54,359
We were out for a ride in a carriage.

47
00:05:54,521 --> 00:05:56,194
The carriage again?

48
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:05,532
I want to kiss you.

49
00:06:11,246 --> 00:06:13,544
- You have an early day tomorrow.
- Why?

50
00:06:13,665 --> 00:06:15,918
- To pack our bags.
- We're going somewhere?

51
00:06:16,042 --> 00:06:17,214
- Yes.
- Where?

52
00:06:17,377 --> 00:06:19,971
It's a surprise
for our wedding anniversary.

53
00:06:20,255 --> 00:06:24,726
Our happiness has lasted a year already,
“and the suns of yesteryear...”

54
00:06:24,843 --> 00:06:26,220
What about the hospital?

55
00:06:26,344 --> 00:06:28,438
I want to forget about work
for a few days

56
00:06:28,555 --> 00:06:30,478
and think only of you.

57
00:06:36,855 --> 00:06:38,698
Happy?

58
00:06:38,815 --> 00:06:40,488
Especially when you're here.

59
00:06:40,609 --> 00:06:43,237
I wish you could be
near me every second.

60
00:06:58,168 --> 00:06:59,795
No, please.

61
00:07:01,463 --> 00:07:02,965
Sleep well.

62
00:07:05,884 --> 00:07:07,386
Good night.

63
00:07:21,274 --> 00:07:22,867
Forgive me.

64
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:27,240
You're so good,
so understanding, but I -

65
00:07:27,489 --> 00:07:29,742
It's all right. Go to sleep.

66
00:07:41,211 --> 00:07:43,384
You coming
to the party at the hotel?

67
00:07:43,505 --> 00:07:45,883
I don't know.
Husson goes to bed at sundown.

68
00:07:46,007 --> 00:07:49,637
Then come alone.
They say it's going to snow tonight.

69
00:07:49,803 --> 00:07:53,103
I'd love to see the mesmerist.
I hear he's wonderful.

70
00:07:53,223 --> 00:07:54,770
I won't let him put me to sleep.

71
00:07:54,891 --> 00:07:58,486
A mesmerist isn't a hypnotist.
He makes the sun rise.

72
00:07:58,645 --> 00:08:01,819
A hypnotist plunges you
down into the depths.

73
00:08:01,982 --> 00:08:04,576
Well, see you later.

74
00:08:16,371 --> 00:08:18,214
What time is it?

75
00:08:18,623 --> 00:08:21,672
Five o'clock. You look bored.
Don't let me keep you.

76
00:08:21,793 --> 00:08:23,670
One's never bored in a bar,

77
00:08:23,837 --> 00:08:27,262
unlike in a church,
alone with one's own soul.

78
00:08:28,174 --> 00:08:30,723
I have something nice to tell you.

79
00:08:31,511 --> 00:08:33,013
I love you.

80
00:08:34,806 --> 00:08:36,934
Your scars heal so nicely.

81
00:08:37,058 --> 00:08:38,685
Oh, stop it.

82
00:08:46,484 --> 00:08:48,202
Let's not go in.
She's with Husson.

83
00:08:48,319 --> 00:08:49,821
Too late. He saw us.

84
00:08:49,946 --> 00:08:52,825
What have you got against him?
He's an interesting fellow.

85
00:08:52,949 --> 00:08:55,418
I don't like how he looks at me.

86
00:08:55,535 --> 00:08:56,957
Come on.

87
00:09:13,678 --> 00:09:16,181
I saw you two
pass by earlier arm in arm.

88
00:09:16,306 --> 00:09:19,185
It was a pleasure to see.
Like newly-weds.

89
00:09:19,309 --> 00:09:22,654
- We must have looked ridiculous.
- No, it was very reassuring,

90
00:09:22,771 --> 00:09:25,240
like an everyday occurrence.

91
00:09:25,398 --> 00:09:29,744
But you, Pierre - you sometimes
make me feel guilty and uneasy.

92
00:09:30,028 --> 00:09:32,030
You and I are so different.

93
00:09:32,155 --> 00:09:35,159
One really doesn't meet
many men like you.

94
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:37,827
I mean it sincerely.

95
00:09:50,298 --> 00:09:53,268
Another missed opportunity
for punishment.

96
00:09:53,384 --> 00:09:55,762
Why? Do you know them?

97
00:09:56,137 --> 00:09:57,730
Is that all you're interested in?

98
00:09:57,847 --> 00:10:00,350
Everything else is useless.
A lot of wasted time.

99
00:10:00,475 --> 00:10:03,775
You should see a specialist
about your obsessions.

100
00:10:03,895 --> 00:10:07,399
He's rich and idle.
Those are his two main illnesses.

101
00:10:07,774 --> 00:10:09,276
Don't forget the hunt.

102
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:12,904
I also have
a special weakness for the poor.

103
00:10:13,029 --> 00:10:16,659
I think of them when it snows,
with no fur coats, no hope. Nothing.

104
00:10:16,783 --> 00:10:18,535
You're very attractive, Séverine.

105
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:20,958
Your compliments are too subtle,
so just be quiet.

106
00:10:21,079 --> 00:10:22,626
You're asking the impossible.

107
00:10:22,789 --> 00:10:26,168
I've been here three hours.
I feel a headache coming on.

108
00:10:26,292 --> 00:10:28,420
It's not too cold outside?
- No, it's nice.

109
00:10:28,545 --> 00:10:31,139
I'll get some fresh air before dark.
See you later, Renée.

110
00:10:31,256 --> 00:10:33,475
- See you later.
- Have a nice walk.

111
00:10:37,804 --> 00:10:39,977
I like him. He's amusing.

112
00:10:40,390 --> 00:10:41,892
He's strange.

113
00:10:42,058 --> 00:10:43,731
Worse than that.

114
00:11:05,331 --> 00:11:08,005
- Forgot to ask how Husson is.
- He's fine.

115
00:11:08,126 --> 00:11:11,005
- Still together?
- Afraid so. Let's not talk about it.

116
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:14,299
You remember Henriette?
- Yes, very well.

117
00:11:15,175 --> 00:11:16,927
It seems...

118
00:11:17,844 --> 00:11:19,846
she's turning tricks.

119
00:11:19,971 --> 00:11:22,349
- What?
- In one of those houses.

120
00:11:22,515 --> 00:11:24,893
They say she's there
several days a week.

121
00:11:26,019 --> 00:11:28,147
Can you believe it? Henriette!

122
00:11:29,022 --> 00:11:31,775
Of course,
that's all so far from your world.

123
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:35,699
But can you imagine?
A woman like you or me.

124
00:11:36,821 --> 00:11:39,119
Can you see her
going with just anybody?

125
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,743
In those places
you don't get to choose.

126
00:11:41,868 --> 00:11:44,712
Old or not, lousy-looking or not.

127
00:11:45,371 --> 00:11:49,217
Even with a man you love
it can be unpleasant.

128
00:11:49,334 --> 00:11:53,259
It must be horrible with a stranger.
Those places still exist?

129
00:11:53,880 --> 00:11:56,224
Excuse me, ladies,

130
00:11:56,341 --> 00:11:59,845
but I can assure you:
Those places do still exist.

131
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:03,439
Oh, maybe not like
the joints before the war.

132
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:06,400
The red lights are gone, of course.

133
00:12:06,684 --> 00:12:09,813
But trust me:
There's no lack of business.

134
00:12:10,271 --> 00:12:12,365
I could show you a good half dozen.

135
00:12:12,607 --> 00:12:14,530
Part of my job, you see.

136
00:12:14,651 --> 00:12:18,246
In 20 years of driving a cab
I've seen everything.

137
00:12:18,905 --> 00:12:21,033
I've been mugged twice,

138
00:12:21,157 --> 00:12:23,330
and I'm none the worse for it.

139
00:12:26,412 --> 00:12:28,414
Hey, what's the matter?

140
00:12:28,581 --> 00:12:30,083
We're here.

141
00:13:04,826 --> 00:13:06,794
These flowers came for you, madame.

142
00:13:06,953 --> 00:13:08,955
Very well. Who sent them?

143
00:13:09,122 --> 00:13:10,874
Mr. Husson.

144
00:13:19,465 --> 00:13:21,467
Why did you put them here?

145
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:33,487
I'll get a cloth.

146
00:13:33,771 --> 00:13:36,274
It's nothing.
The water was clean.

147
00:14:05,178 --> 00:14:07,180
What's the matter with me today?

148
00:14:07,764 --> 00:14:09,607
Séverine, come quickly!

149
00:14:15,313 --> 00:14:17,407
Are you coming or not?

150
00:14:28,993 --> 00:14:32,088
- Will you be much longer?
- I'm almost done.

151
00:14:45,426 --> 00:14:47,804
Can I ask you a silly question?

152
00:14:47,970 --> 00:14:49,472
Go ahead.

153
00:14:53,226 --> 00:14:55,069
Before you met me,

154
00:14:55,186 --> 00:14:58,281
did you use to go
to those... houses a lot?

155
00:14:58,898 --> 00:15:00,571
Those houses?

156
00:15:02,527 --> 00:15:06,077
Not very often. Why?
Does that interest you?

157
00:15:06,197 --> 00:15:08,325
Everything about you interests me.

158
00:15:09,784 --> 00:15:12,207
But I thought
they'd been closed down.

159
00:15:12,328 --> 00:15:14,330
They've gone underground.

160
00:15:15,415 --> 00:15:17,634
I can't imagine how it works.

161
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:20,594
- Listen, I have to work.

162
00:15:23,256 --> 00:15:26,385
Well, you go in.
The women are there.

163
00:15:26,843 --> 00:15:28,390
You pick one.

164
00:15:28,511 --> 00:15:31,014
You spend half an hour
alone with her,

165
00:15:31,139 --> 00:15:34,143
and after you leave,
you're depressed all day.

166
00:15:34,267 --> 00:15:37,862
But what can you do?<i>
Semen retentum venenum est.</i>

167
00:15:37,979 --> 00:15:39,481
Be quiet.

168
00:15:40,398 --> 00:15:43,117
I don't want to hear
any more, please.

169
00:15:43,985 --> 00:15:45,658
What's the matter?

170
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:52,790
I've never seen you like this.
What's going on?

171
00:15:52,952 --> 00:15:55,455
Nothing.
I'm just tired and on edge.

172
00:15:56,038 --> 00:15:57,585
Go get some rest.

173
00:15:57,707 --> 00:15:59,209
You're right.

174
00:16:03,129 --> 00:16:05,427
- Shall I come with you?

175
00:16:05,548 --> 00:16:08,643
Yes, stay with me
until I fall asleep.

176
00:16:11,137 --> 00:16:13,265
Will you never grow up?

177
00:16:33,659 --> 00:16:36,037
I can't hit anything today.
Take my place.

178
00:16:36,162 --> 00:16:39,006
- You leaving?
- No, <i>I'll</i> wait for you inside.

179
00:16:49,709 --> 00:16:51,762
- How are you?
- Not bad.

180
00:16:51,886 --> 00:16:54,935
- We don't see much of you these days.
- That's true.

181
00:17:02,522 --> 00:17:04,866
<i>The mysterious Henriette!</i>

182
00:17:09,195 --> 00:17:11,243
<i>The woman with two faces.</i>

183
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:14,117
A double life. How intriguing!

184
00:17:14,700 --> 00:17:18,170
Did Renée tell you?
- Yes. But why?

185
00:17:18,371 --> 00:17:20,373
Simple: for the money.

186
00:17:20,957 --> 00:17:25,007
Most women who sell themselves
do so, alas, for the money.

187
00:17:27,922 --> 00:17:32,644
It's nice to see you, Séverine.
- I can't understand women like that.

188
00:17:32,885 --> 00:17:35,058
It's the oldest profession
in the world.

189
00:17:35,221 --> 00:17:36,894
It's mostly arranged by phone now,

190
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:39,809
but the women in those houses
are a special breed.

191
00:17:40,309 --> 00:17:42,152
I'm sure you know them well.

192
00:17:43,020 --> 00:17:45,773
Yes, I used to go a lot.
I enjoyed it.

193
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:49,653
There's a very special atmosphere.
The women are complete slaves.

194
00:17:49,986 --> 00:17:52,409
I remember a few around the Opera.

195
00:17:52,572 --> 00:17:55,121
Especially one run by Anais.

196
00:17:55,241 --> 00:17:58,871
11 , cite' Jean de Saumur.
I have marvellous memories.

197
00:17:58,995 --> 00:18:01,168
- Are you mad?
- It's nothing.

198
00:18:01,289 --> 00:18:03,883
A cute <i>compulsion</i>, as the English say.

199
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:06,423
An insignificant little impulse.

200
00:18:06,711 --> 00:18:08,930
I must see you sometime -

201
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:11,014
without your husband, of course.

202
00:18:11,132 --> 00:18:14,477
I admire Pierre very much,
but I'd prefer he not be there.

203
00:18:23,686 --> 00:18:27,156
<i>Madame Anafg
11, cite Jean de Saamuz:</i>

204
00:21:13,981 --> 00:21:15,949
<i>What's the matter with you?</i>

205
00:21:54,021 --> 00:21:56,490
- I wanted to speak to you.
- Come in.

206
00:22:01,821 --> 00:22:04,074
Are you in charge of...?

207
00:22:04,198 --> 00:22:05,996
I'm Madame Anais.

208
00:22:06,325 --> 00:22:08,874
I came to see if -

209
00:22:08,994 --> 00:22:11,713
Let's go inside.
We'll be more comfortable there.

210
00:22:18,003 --> 00:22:20,927
Have a seat.
Can I offer you something?

211
00:22:22,341 --> 00:22:24,810
- Cigarette?
- Thank you, I don't smoke.

212
00:22:25,427 --> 00:22:28,476
Don't be frightened.
Make yourself at home.

213
00:22:28,889 --> 00:22:31,608
I'll do whatever I can.
Sit down.

214
00:22:35,187 --> 00:22:39,033
You're nice, and fresh.
Just what they like here.

215
00:22:39,525 --> 00:22:42,244
I know it's hard at first,

216
00:22:42,361 --> 00:22:45,240
but who doesn't need money
now and then?

217
00:22:46,949 --> 00:22:49,372
We'll split fifty-fifty.

218
00:22:50,119 --> 00:22:51,917
I have my expenses.

219
00:22:52,037 --> 00:22:54,961
Thank you very much,
but I must be going.

220
00:22:56,125 --> 00:22:58,628
Come now.
You're just a bit nervous.

221
00:23:01,088 --> 00:23:03,591
I bet it's the first time
you've worked.

222
00:23:03,966 --> 00:23:06,139
It's not really so awful.

223
00:23:06,594 --> 00:23:09,598
It's still early.
The other girls aren't here yet.

224
00:23:09,722 --> 00:23:11,770
You're about to lose a button.

225
00:23:12,725 --> 00:23:14,648
When would you like to start?

226
00:23:14,768 --> 00:23:16,315
I don't know.

227
00:23:16,437 --> 00:23:17,734
Today?

228
00:23:17,855 --> 00:23:20,654
Yes, perhaps.
But afternoons only.

229
00:23:20,774 --> 00:23:24,074
I have to leave at five, without fail.

230
00:23:24,570 --> 00:23:26,038
All right,

231
00:23:26,155 --> 00:23:29,534
but you must be punctual
or I'll be very annoyed.

232
00:23:30,075 --> 00:23:32,669
I promise
you'll be free to go at five.

233
00:23:34,079 --> 00:23:35,797
Good-bye, and excuse me.

234
00:23:35,915 --> 00:23:38,634
I'll expect you this afternoon at two.

235
00:23:57,478 --> 00:23:59,230
What's the matter?
Anything serious?

236
00:23:59,355 --> 00:24:01,778
No, I was out shopping

237
00:24:01,941 --> 00:24:03,943
and just suddenly wanted
to see you.

238
00:24:04,068 --> 00:24:07,413
- I thought you didn't like hospitals.
- No, I don't.

239
00:24:07,696 --> 00:24:10,791
I don't feel like being alone.
Let me take you out to lunch.

240
00:24:10,908 --> 00:24:14,412
I'm having lunch with the manager.
I told you this morning.

241
00:24:14,536 --> 00:24:16,789
- That's true, but -
- I'm sorry.

242
00:24:17,456 --> 00:24:20,050
Don't forget we're going out
with the Févrets tonight.

243
00:24:21,710 --> 00:24:24,429
- Sorry to bother you.
- Bother me?

244
00:24:24,546 --> 00:24:27,641
See you tonight.
<i>I'll</i> try to be home early.

245
00:25:17,850 --> 00:25:19,898
I didn't think you'd be back.

246
00:25:20,019 --> 00:25:22,772
You left so abruptly this morning.

247
00:25:23,022 --> 00:25:25,775
I thought I'd scared you off.
Come in.

248
00:25:29,987 --> 00:25:31,864
Put your things in here.

249
00:25:34,783 --> 00:25:37,206
You'll meet the other two girls soon.

250
00:25:37,327 --> 00:25:39,750
Mathilde and Charlotte.

251
00:25:39,872 --> 00:25:41,874
Both very nice.

252
00:25:42,791 --> 00:25:45,635
I only tolerate
well-bred people here,

253
00:25:45,753 --> 00:25:47,881
and they must be cheerful.

254
00:25:48,464 --> 00:25:51,013
I want people to enjoy their work.

255
