01:10:40,111 --> 01:10:43,240
- So?
- So next time we won't wait.

776
01:10:43,614 --> 01:10:46,618
- We almost didn't come today either.

777
01:10:47,118 --> 01:10:49,041
Your cut keeps going up.

778
01:10:49,162 --> 01:10:51,506
We're getting sick of you
and your little thug.

779
01:10:52,123 --> 01:10:55,502
Don't fight with these hoodlums.
Settle down.

780
01:10:55,626 --> 01:10:59,551
Gentlemen, if you have
something to settle, go outside.

781
01:10:59,672 --> 01:11:01,720
Shut your trap, you.

782
01:11:02,967 --> 01:11:05,766
The snow.
We know you've got it.

783
01:11:12,351 --> 01:11:14,399
Now don't let us keep you.

784
01:11:17,148 --> 01:11:19,822
We'll discuss that “thug” remark
some other time.

785
01:11:19,942 --> 01:11:21,535
As you like.

786
01:11:51,390 --> 01:11:53,813
Pierrot, another bottle.

787
01:12:03,736 --> 01:12:05,784
- Where you going?
- To make a call.

788
01:12:05,905 --> 01:12:07,327
Again?

789
01:12:11,118 --> 01:12:13,792
Birds... what a curse!

790
01:12:13,913 --> 01:12:17,383
You can say that again.
He's got it bad.

791
01:12:17,500 --> 01:12:19,594
It's cost him dearly before.

792
01:12:19,710 --> 01:12:23,214
But it's always been his weakness.
Nothing I can do.

793
01:12:23,881 --> 01:12:26,350
Anais? It's Marcel.

794
01:12:26,843 --> 01:12:28,390
Any news?

795
01:12:29,971 --> 01:12:31,518
When?

796
01:12:31,848 --> 01:12:33,350
Really?

797
01:12:35,393 --> 01:12:37,145
I'll be right there.

798
01:12:44,360 --> 01:12:47,990
“Carried his father on his back.”
Six letters.

799
01:12:48,865 --> 01:12:51,163
The third letter's an N.

800
01:12:51,993 --> 01:12:54,746
“Aeneas,” with A-E at the start.

801
01:12:54,871 --> 01:12:58,341
Ah, right.
That comes up a lot in crosswords.

802
01:13:00,209 --> 01:13:03,213
Belle, it's him again.
He's waiting.

803
01:13:15,473 --> 01:13:17,526
How are you?

804
01:13:23,190 --> 01:13:26,069
Where were you?
Why did you go away?

805
01:13:26,402 --> 01:13:29,827
I had to leave Paris for a few days.
I can explain.

806
01:13:29,947 --> 01:13:33,952
I'll explain a few things too,
and I'll leave my signature as well.

807
01:13:41,250 --> 01:13:42,968
Don't touch my face.

808
01:13:44,587 --> 01:13:46,260
Don't touch me!

809
01:13:47,089 --> 01:13:49,933
Do that once more
and you'll never see me again.

810
01:13:52,970 --> 01:13:54,813
Very well... this time.

811
01:14:20,206 --> 01:14:22,129
I missed you, you know.

812
01:14:23,292 --> 01:14:26,091
I shouldn't tell you this,
but I waited for you.

813
01:14:26,629 --> 01:14:30,008
I want to see you more often now.
At night too.

814
01:14:30,132 --> 01:14:32,635
I'm here every day.
Isn't that enough?

815
01:14:33,302 --> 01:14:35,851
You know I'm not free.
- I don't give a damn.

816
01:14:49,485 --> 01:14:51,283
I don't get it.

817
01:14:52,363 --> 01:14:54,365
You seem to like being with me.

818
01:14:54,490 --> 01:14:56,083
Very much...

819
01:14:56,200 --> 01:14:58,168
but it's not enough.

820
01:14:58,327 --> 01:15:00,329
You love the other fellow?

821
01:15:01,831 --> 01:15:03,708
Then why are you here?

822
01:15:03,833 --> 01:15:05,335
I don't know.

823
01:15:05,459 --> 01:15:07,507
They're two different things.

824
01:15:32,194 --> 01:15:34,196
I'm starving.
Where should we eat?

825
01:15:34,321 --> 01:15:36,369
No idea.
We'll decide on the way.

826
01:15:36,490 --> 01:15:39,118
I'll be back at three.

827
01:15:40,578 --> 01:15:43,172
You've changed so much.
I hardly recognise you.

828
01:15:43,289 --> 01:15:46,668
It's so nice to see you smile.
- I do feel much better.

829
01:15:46,792 --> 01:15:49,511
I've never seen you like this.
If only -

830
01:15:49,628 --> 01:15:50,675
What?

831
01:15:50,796 --> 01:15:54,141
If only one day you had
some great news for me.

832
01:15:54,258 --> 01:15:56,932
- What do you mean?
- You know very well.

833
01:15:57,053 --> 01:15:59,772
What I want
more than anything: a child.

834
01:16:15,821 --> 01:16:18,165
- What are you looking at?
- Nothing.

835
01:16:19,325 --> 01:16:22,875
This old thing caught my eye.
I don't know why. It's strange.

836
01:16:22,995 --> 01:16:26,215
- Nothing strange about it.
- No, you're right.

837
01:16:34,173 --> 01:16:37,427
You're back!
I didn't recognise you.

838
01:16:37,551 --> 01:16:41,601
Did you forget about us,
you ungrateful devil? It's been ages.

839
01:16:42,056 --> 01:16:44,229
But you haven't changed.

840
01:16:44,433 --> 01:16:46,276
First door on the right.

841
01:16:50,356 --> 01:16:53,781
Come on, girls.
An old friend is back.

842
01:16:54,693 --> 01:16:58,618
Well? Let's go.

843
01:17:03,285 --> 01:17:06,038
Yes, yes, you look lovely.

844
01:17:07,623 --> 01:17:11,799
- You 're flattering me.
- No, sir, I remember you well.

845
01:17:11,961 --> 01:17:14,965
I even dream about you sometimes.

846
01:17:16,090 --> 01:17:18,058
I don't like the sound of that.

847
01:17:18,175 --> 01:17:21,850
- No, I couldn't.
- I insist. Do me the pleasure.

848
01:17:25,683 --> 01:17:28,277
Hello, ladies. Sit down.

849
01:17:32,106 --> 01:17:35,155
Belle de jour? That's original.

850
01:17:36,694 --> 01:17:38,822
Perhaps you'd like some refreshment.

851
01:17:39,321 --> 01:17:41,164
Later.

852
01:17:42,324 --> 01:17:44,122
Nothing's changed here.

853
01:17:44,243 --> 01:17:46,746
Still the same homely welcome...

854
01:17:47,496 --> 01:17:49,169
the same drapes.

855
01:17:50,499 --> 01:17:53,594
Whatever happened to that girl,
the lion tamer?

856
01:17:55,004 --> 01:17:56,677
I haven't heard from her.

857
01:17:56,797 --> 01:18:00,597
- And the heat's up all the way?
- You haven't changed either.

858
01:18:00,718 --> 01:18:02,846
Look, that armchair.

859
01:18:05,014 --> 01:18:06,516
It was snowing...

860
01:18:07,308 --> 01:18:09,527
The same special fragrance
in the air.

861
01:18:09,685 --> 01:18:11,437
Still jasmine.

862
01:18:12,062 --> 01:18:14,565
I hope you have some time for us.

863
01:18:14,690 --> 01:18:17,193
All my life.
I'm a man of leisure.

864
01:18:18,194 --> 01:18:19,491
Now, then...

865
01:18:19,612 --> 01:18:21,990
I'd like to be alone with Belle de jour.

866
01:18:27,828 --> 01:18:29,796
No, I won't!

867
01:18:29,914 --> 01:18:32,884
Is this any way to behave?
You'll stay.

868
01:18:36,045 --> 01:18:37,888
She's very sweet.

869
01:18:39,215 --> 01:18:41,217
Just a little on edge sometimes.

870
01:18:44,887 --> 01:18:46,389
Happy now?

871
01:18:46,889 --> 01:18:49,517
Don't tell me it's coincidence.
You knew I was here.

872
01:18:49,642 --> 01:18:51,144
You're wrong.

873
01:18:51,310 --> 01:18:54,063
It's your fault.
You gave me this address.

874
01:18:54,855 --> 01:18:57,529
- You're wrong.
- Come closer and I'll scream.

875
01:18:57,650 --> 01:18:59,573
I'll jump out the window!

876
01:19:05,866 --> 01:19:07,118
Is this your bed?

877
01:19:07,243 --> 01:19:09,120
You disgust me.
I already told you that.

878
01:19:09,245 --> 01:19:12,374
Yes, it's my bed.
What else do you want to know?

879
01:19:13,457 --> 01:19:15,425
You like being humiliated.

880
01:19:15,542 --> 01:19:17,089
I don't.

881
01:19:18,504 --> 01:19:20,222
Don't tell Pierre.

882
01:19:21,739 --> 01:19:24,234
I admire him more and more.

883
01:19:25,302 --> 01:19:27,350
Please don't tell him.

884
01:19:27,888 --> 01:19:30,141
At least try to understand.

885
01:19:30,266 --> 01:19:32,234
I'm lost.

886
01:19:32,351 --> 01:19:35,821
I can't help it. I can't fight it.

887
01:19:36,772 --> 01:19:40,072
I know I'll have to atone
for everything one day.

888
01:19:40,693 --> 01:19:42,787
But I couldn't live without it.

889
01:19:44,780 --> 01:19:47,124
Fine. Do as you like with me.

890
01:19:48,951 --> 01:19:50,919
No. Not now, anyway.

891
01:19:51,036 --> 01:19:55,416
I guess what attracted me
about you was your virtue.

892
01:19:55,541 --> 01:19:57,635
You were the wife of a boy scout.

893
01:19:57,751 --> 01:19:59,753
That's all changed now.

894
01:19:59,878 --> 01:20:02,222
I have principles, unlike you.

895
01:20:02,464 --> 01:20:05,138
I won't tell Pierre, of course.

896
01:20:06,468 --> 01:20:10,473
But I have friends I could tell.
I could send you some business.

897
01:20:11,473 --> 01:20:13,646
Sorry I don't feel like it.

898
01:20:13,767 --> 01:20:15,769
It really doesn't appeal at all.

899
01:20:16,895 --> 01:20:18,897
Another time, perhaps.

900
01:20:19,148 --> 01:20:20,650
Who knows?

901
01:20:20,774 --> 01:20:22,776
I won't take up your time.

902
01:20:30,200 --> 01:20:33,625
This isn't for you.
Get Pierre some chocolates for me.

903
01:21:23,170 --> 01:21:25,218
Ready? Go!

904
01:21:30,386 --> 01:21:31,888
Prepare!

905
01:21:32,388 --> 01:21:33,389
Fire!

906
01:22:12,428 --> 01:22:14,601
- He left already?

907
01:22:15,264 --> 01:22:16,982
May I speak with you?

908
01:22:18,267 --> 01:22:19,735
Run along.

909
01:22:27,151 --> 01:22:29,074
- I have to leave.
- When?

910
01:22:29,194 --> 01:22:30,491
Now.

911
01:22:30,612 --> 01:22:32,990
- But you'll be back?
- Definitely not.

912
01:22:33,115 --> 01:22:34,617
Why?

913
01:22:35,159 --> 01:22:37,412
You could have told me sooner.

914
01:22:37,536 --> 01:22:41,416
Aren't you happy here?
- Yes, fine. It's just -

915
01:22:41,540 --> 01:22:43,133
Now I get it.

916
01:22:44,877 --> 01:22:46,379
It's Marcel.

917
01:22:47,379 --> 01:22:49,507
He was just here.
He was furious.

918
01:22:49,715 --> 01:22:51,968
Almost barged into your room.

919
01:22:52,676 --> 01:22:54,974
There's something odd there.

920
01:22:56,096 --> 01:22:57,939
Has he demanding?

921
01:22:58,056 --> 01:23:02,482
Wants you to be his alone,
day and night?

922
01:23:05,814 --> 01:23:07,942
It's always the same story with men.

923
01:23:09,401 --> 01:23:11,654
You're right. You'd better go.

924
01:23:12,446 --> 01:23:15,040
There could be trouble one day.

925
01:23:16,116 --> 01:23:17,868
But I'll miss you.

926
01:23:18,744 --> 01:23:20,496
Women like you...

927
01:23:21,497 --> 01:23:23,374
You and I got along well.

928
01:23:23,749 --> 01:23:25,092
It's true.

929
01:23:25,209 --> 01:23:29,055
Let me know how you're doing.
Call once in a while.

930
01:23:29,338 --> 01:23:31,011
I'd like that-.

931
01:23:31,173 --> 01:23:33,221
Is there some address -

932
01:23:34,718 --> 01:23:37,016
Too bad.
What else can I say?

933
01:24:47,583 --> 01:24:50,086
Madame,
there's a gentleman to see you.

934
01:24:52,129 --> 01:24:53,472
Who is it?
Do you know him?

935
01:24:53,589 --> 01:24:56,468
No, but he says it's urgent.

936
01:25:06,018 --> 01:25:08,521
- Did you bring the catalogue?

937
01:25:08,645 --> 01:25:10,943
Sit down.

938
01:25:12,941 --> 01:25:15,114
Not bad, the catalogue thing.

939
01:25:17,696 --> 01:25:19,448
I like your little pad.

940
01:25:19,573 --> 01:25:21,871
What are you doing here?
You're mad! Go away!

941
01:25:21,992 --> 01:25:25,997
Since you weren't at Anais' anymore,
I thought I'd pay you a visit,

942
01:25:26,121 --> 01:25:27,998
see how you're doing.

943
01:25:28,874 --> 01:25:31,297
- How did you find me?
- Child's play.

944
01:25:31,793 --> 01:25:33,636
Is this your husband?

945
01:25:33,795 --> 01:25:36,594
Good-looking.
A nice fellow.

946
01:25:37,049 --> 01:25:38,722
A lot better than me.

947
01:25:38,842 --> 01:25:41,061
- Please leave.
- Don't worry.

948
01:25:41,178 --> 01:25:43,180
I won't make a scene.

949
01:25:43,555 --> 01:25:46,058
I just want to know why you left.

950
01:25:46,183 --> 01:25:49,483
You hear me?
- Be quiet. The maid will hear.

951
01:25:49,686 --> 01:25:51,688
Go away. He'll be home soon.

952
01:25:52,481 --> 01:25:55,109
I just got here
and you want me to leave?

953
01:25:55,233 --> 01:25:57,110
- What do you want?
- To see you again.

954
01:25:57,235 --> 01:26:00,114
Impossible.
I'm never going back there.

955
01:26:05,160 --> 01:26:07,162
I'll give you three days.

956
01:26:07,287 --> 01:26:09,255
Find some excuse.

957
01:26:09,498 --> 01:26:12,843
I'll be waiting at the Hétel Du Bois
on rue Fromentin.

958
01:26:13,043 --> 01:26:16,343
You'll spend the night with me.
- Impossible.

959
01:26:21,343 --> 01:26:23,892
Very well. I'll wait for him.

960
01:26:26,306 --> 01:26:28,684
I have a lot to tell him.
- You wouldn't dare.

961
01:26:28,809 --> 01:26:30,186
Yes, I would.

962
01:26:30,352 --> 01:26:33,856
I didn't want it to come to this,
but since you're forcing me -

963
01:26:34,022 --> 01:26:36,241
I guess it's just as well.

964
01:26:36,858 --> 01:26:39,737
I'd decided to tell him anyway.
- Really?

965
01:26:39,861 --> 01:26:42,034
He'd have found out
sooner or later.

966
01:26:42,197 --> 01:26:44,541
One of our friends
discovered I was there.

967
01:26:44,741 --> 01:26:47,085
I want to get it all off my chest.

968
01:26:48,829 --> 01:26:51,173
Fine. We'll both wait for him

969
01:26:51,289 --> 01:26:55,135
and tell him together.
I don't mind.

970
01:27:04,511 --> 01:27:07,981
I'm begging you: Leave!
He'll be home soon.

971
01:27:21,403 --> 01:27:22,905
Don't worry.

972
01:27:23,655 --> 01:27:25,282
I'll leave.

973
01:27:26,199 --> 01:27:29,203
I didn't believe you,
but I'm starting to understand.

974
01:27:33,915 --> 01:27:35,917
Here's the obstacle.

975
01:27:44,509 --> 01:27:47,262
See you soon...

976
01:28:23,173 --> 01:28:26,302
- Did you see her?
- Let me have the car.

977
01:28:26,676 --> 01:28:28,895
- Where are you going?
- I need it.

978
01:28:29,471 --> 01:28:31,974
Let me have the car, and beat it.

979
01:28:32,432 --> 01:28:34,480
What are you up to now?

980
01:28:35,727 --> 01:28:37,400
I said beat it.

981
01:28:38,104 --> 01:28:41,654
This time you've seen
the last of me, kid.

982
01:30:05,817 --> 01:30:08,661
Oh no, you don't.
You're not running off.

983
01:30:58,954 --> 01:30:59,955
Any news?

984
01:31:00,080 --> 01:31:02,424
The killer's dead,
and the police are baffled.

985
01:31:02,540 --> 01:31:05,134
Either he shot the wrong man
or he was insane.

986
01:31:05,251 --> 01:31:07,299
- Has he been identified?
- Yes, a common crook.

987
01:31:07,462 --> 01:31:10,306
It wasn't his first murder.
- Strange.

988
01:31:10,465 --> 01:31:12,809
- How is Sérizy?
- Too early to say.

989
01:31:12,926 --> 01:31:14,928
His wife's in the waiting room.

990
01:31:36,408 --> 01:31:37,876
How is he?

991
01:31:37,993 --> 01:31:41,338
It's too early to say,
but he'll live, so try to relax.

992
01:31:41,496 --> 01:31:44,500
- Can I see him?
- No, he's still in a coma.

993
01:31:44,624 --> 01:31:45,876
Perhaps tomorrow.

994
01:31:46,001 --> 01:31:49,346
You should go home and try to rest.

995
01:31:49,504 --> 01:31:52,633
We'll give you an hourly report,
I promise.

996
01:31:54,426 --> 01:31:56,019
Don't worry.

997
01:32:00,098 --> 01:32:02,396
Come on. I'll see you home.

998
01:33:11,086 --> 01:33:13,305
I sent Maria for the newspapers.

999
01:33:13,755 --> 01:33:16,804
I know the articles you like.
I'll read them to you.

1000
01:33:18,760 --> 01:33:22,390
Maria's very nice,
and she's so fond of you.

1001
01:33:25,767 --> 01:33:27,815
Everyone's asking about you.

1002
01:33:30,271 --> 01:33:33,901
You're getting better, you know.
The doctor's very optimistic.

1003
01:33:34,818 --> 01:33:37,742
You don't realise it,
but you've made great progress.

1004
01:33:37,862 --> 01:33:39,660
Your eyes especially.

1005
01:33:41,199 --> 01:33:43,543
It's funny.
Ever since you were -

1006
01:33:43,660 --> 01:33:47,164
Ever since your accident,
my dreams have stopped.

1007
01:33:48,873 --> 01:33:51,717
I think it's time for your drops.

1008
01:34:18,319 --> 01:34:21,539
Mr. Husson, madame.
He'd like to see your husband.

1009
01:34:27,287 --> 01:34:28,789
I'm coming.

1010
01:34:41,593 --> 01:34:43,516
I'm sorry to bother you.

1011
01:34:43,845 --> 01:34:45,688
You want to see Pierre?

1012
01:34:45,805 --> 01:34:47,478
Just for a moment.

1013
01:34:47,932 --> 01:34:50,526
You know, he still can't speak.

1014
01:34:50,977 --> 01:34:52,650
I know.

1015
01:34:52,770 --> 01:34:54,693
I'm sorry I couldn't come sooner.

1016
01:34:54,814 --> 01:34:57,693
You know how I admire Pierre,
but I was out of town.

1017
01:34:58,109 --> 01:34:59,986
Pretty dress.

1018
01:35:00,820 --> 01:35:03,619
You look like
a precocious schoolgirl.

1019
01:35:05,241 --> 01:35:08,245
- What do you want to tell Pierre?
- Everything I know about you.

1020
01:35:08,369 --> 01:35:09,461
What?

1021
01:35:09,579 --> 01:35:11,126
Calm down.

1022
01:35:12,248 --> 01:35:16,344
He's paralysed now,
completely dependent on you.

1023
01:35:18,213 --> 01:35:21,717
He's ashamed of being a burden
on such a virtuous wife,

1024
01:35:21,841 --> 01:35:24,845
so I've decided
to tell him everything.

1025
01:35:25,678 --> 01:35:29,057
He'll be hurt, but I think
I'll be doing him a favour.

1026
01:35:31,684 --> 01:35:34,528
Who could call me cruel after that?

1027
01:35:37,398 --> 01:35:39,150
Take me to him, please.

1028
01:35:41,778 --> 01:35:43,280
He's in there.

1029
01:35:48,868 --> 01:35:51,872
